Yeah, today I'm flying this plane.
First complaint: We need cute flight logs. Black is too boring, and the pink isn't even pink; it's more like salmon.
I've wanted to fly since I was little.
Today my dream came true… I flew a plane today. I still can't believe it.
FlightAware data.
Saturday I plan to try again. Now the weather doesn't look good, but it's only Monday today.
It seems that challenges in this area are already beginning to show. Due to the FAA's stance on certain drugs, I may find it difficult to get my medical certificate.
This is not impossible, but it would require a lot of time and a lot of additional work.
Although this is somewhat disappointing, it's just another problem that needs to be addressed, and currently, it does seem solvable. It's just that it will take a lot of time and money.
If you want to know what challenges I will face next:
FAA doesn't like ADHD. If you're taking medication for ADHD, you definitely won't get a medical certificate.
<https://youtu.be/W5JSfq6LLAU?si=xIxPaY8ayqqNSj4c>
If I ever have the chance to customize the tail number of the plane, it has to be some variant of N1337_, where _ represents any available letter character.
Of course, the sun will still rise when I'm not here, ha ha. What a bummer.
I need to fly again. But this damn weather is not cooperating.
Welcome to the world of general aviation! 😜
